{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01UU9Kt4puX7uPjVH6ZQeUrt","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01EZbKnDAQCAj7X6Ef7AmkjW","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/.ralph/work-summary.txt","content":"# Work Summary — Spec 01: Extract Shared Library\n\n## What was implemented\n\nCreated `lib/x-agent-common.sh` containing all shared boilerplate extracted from existing agents:\n\n### Environment defaults\n- `KEEP_DIR`, `FAIL_FAST`, `CHANGED_FILES`, `TMPDIR_ROOT` with sensible defaults\n- CI-aware `MAX_LINES` (999999 in CI, 40 locally) with explicit override support\n\n### Helper functions\n- `hr()` — separator line\n- `step(name)` — step header with timing\n- `fmt_elapsed()` — elapsed time for current step\n- `should_continue()` — fail-fast guard (requires caller `overall_ok`)\n- `need(tool)` — required tool check, exits 2 if missing\n\n### Setup helpers (not auto-executed)\n- `setup_outdir(agent-name)` — creates temp dir, sets OUTDIR, installs cleanup trap\n- `setup_lock(agent-name)` — workflow lock with flock + perl fallback\n\n### Result formatting\n- `print_result(ok, log_path, fix_hint)` — prints Result: PASS|FAIL with optional Fix: hint\n- `print_overall(overall_ok)` — prints Overall: PASS|FAIL with Logs: path\n\n### install.sh updates\n- Remote installs now fetch `lib/x-agent-common.sh` from the repo\n- `install_lib_to_root()` function installs lib/ directory (symlink for local, copy for remote)\n- Called before skill installation in both Claude and Codex install paths\n\n### run-scenarios.sh updates\n- Shellcheck scope expanded to include `lib/` directory\n\n## Deviations from work plan\n\nNone. All implementation followed the plan exactly.\n\n## Edge cases handled\n- Sourcing produces zero output and no side effects (verified)\n- `need()` exits with code 2 for missing tools (verified)\n- `setup_outdir` cleanup preserves logs on failure or `KEEP_DIR=1` (verified)\n- `setup_outdir` removes temp dir on success with `KEEP_DIR=0` (verified)\n- CI MAX_LINES=999999 with `CI=true` and `CI=1` (verified)\n- Local MAX_LINES=40 when CI unset (verified)\n- Explicit `MAX_LINES` override takes precedence (verified)\n- Lock fallback: flock -> perl -> warning (implemented)\n- All Bash 3.2 compatible (no associative arrays, no readarray, no `|&`)\n\n## Tests written/run\n- Shellcheck passes on `lib/x-agent-common.sh`\n- Source side-effect test: no stdout/stderr on source\n- Function availability: all 9 functions callable after sourcing\n- `need()` exit code: returns 2 for missing tool, passes for existing tool\n- `setup_outdir` cleanup: dir removed on success, preserved on failure, preserved with KEEP_DIR=1\n- `print_result` output format: PASS/FAIL with correct fields\n- `print_overall` output format: Overall PASS/FAIL with Logs: path\n- All 10 existing scenarios pass (shellcheck + 9 agent fixtures)\n\n## Known limitations\n- Existing agents are NOT refactored to use the shared library yet (deferred to spec 02)\n- `run-scenarios.sh` tests don't exercise `lib/x-agent-common.sh` directly; coverage comes from manual smoke tests and future agent adoption\n\n## Exploration notes\nUpdated `.ralph/exploration.md`:\n- Added `lib/x-agent-common.sh` to Key Files & Roles\n- Updated install flow description to reflect lib/ handling\n\n## Lessons Applied This Phase\nNo prior lessons existed. No new lessons required — implementation was straightforward.\n\n## Suggestions for the REVIEW agent\n- Verify the library API matches what spec 02 will need for refactoring existing agents\n- The `print_result` function signature differs slightly from existing inline patterns (agents currently inline the Result/Fix/log printing); spec 02 should decide whether to adopt `print_result` fully or keep inline patterns for agent-specific formatting (e.g., cargo-agent's JSON diagnostics output)\n- The lock pattern in `setup_lock` matches cargo-agent's existing implementation exactly\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":197,"cache_read_input_tokens":73207,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":197},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"226048e6-738a-41d7-adea-ced326c6394c","uuid":"412813a0-0b77-426b-ac42-123bc9a2ae75"}
